This has been strongly urged in Defense of Homer's Miracles; and This is, perhaps, a Defense; not, as Mr. Pope would have it, because Ulysses told a set of foolish Lies to the Phaeacians, who were a very dull Nation; but because the Poet himself wrote to Heathens, to whom poetical Fables were Articles of Faith.
