AMONG other good Uses for which I have thought proper to institute these several introductory Chapters, I have considered these several introductory Chapters as a Kind of Mark or Stamp, which may hereafter enable a very indifferent Reader to distinguish, what is true and genuine in this historic kind of Writing, from what is false and counterfeit.
Indeed it seems likely that some such Mark may shortly become necessary, since the favorable Reception which two or three Authors have lately procured for some such Mark Works of this Nature from the Public, will probably serve as an Encroachment to many others to undertake the like.
